message.content:
Explanation:

- The DELETE /admin/media/{media} route is provided by Route::resource('media', MediaLibraryController::class) in routes/admin.php and maps to MediaLibraryController::destroy.
- The destroy method signature is destroy(Media $medium): RedirectResponse â€” it uses route-model binding to resolve the {media} parameter to an App\Models\Media instance, calls $medium->delete() and returns redirect()->route('admin.media.index')->withSuccess(...).
- A successful deletion therefore results in an HTTP redirect (Laravel RedirectResponse), normally a 302 Found with a Location header pointing to the admin.media.index route (the media index).
- If the {media} cannot be resolved by route-model binding, Laravel will return a 404 Not Found.
- A generic server error may occur in other failure cases, so a 500 response is included as a catch-all.

